<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">M. mandai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. Bulb with a widely separated bifurcate conductor, and a curved embolus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 35" captionStartId="F35" captionText="Figure 35. Merizocera salawa sp. nov., holotype male. A Bulb, dorsal view B bulb, dorsal view, embolus and conductor distorted C palp, prolateral view D palp, retrolateral view. Abbreviations: CO = conductor, CP = cymbial protrusion, EM = embolus." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.53058.figure35" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/443261" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">35B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
